CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 19, 1965, pg. 24 reads: "Big Night - It was a big night for the above youngsters from St. James Center on the West Side. On hand for the first annual Awards Night at the center was Willie Mays, star San Francisco Giants outfielder.  In a surprise appearance Mays presented awards to John Moran (left) and Ernie Davis, winners of the Most Valuable Softball Players Award in Senior and Junior Leagues.  Approximately 400 persons attended the affair. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: San Francisco Giants baseball player Willie Mays, standing between John Moran and Ernie Travis, winners of Most Valuable Softball Players awards
